summary: This mod adds 22 more wood elves to the game, per a user request.  The majority are marriage candidates, are unique and are spread across the province.  No DLC required.
descriptionHtml:
This mod adds 20 more wood elves to the base Skyrim continent, per a user request. Each of these wood elves are unique and are spread throughout the province. Below are a list of each of them and where you might find them (since a few of them wander on the roads):

Dark Brotherhood:
Celehelfin Softthorn - He is a member of the Dark Brotherhood found in the Sanctuary (Can Marry).

Gelweanyl Rosehollow - She is a member of the Dark Brotherhood found in the Sanctuary (Can Marry).

Falkreath:
Tharond Timberhollow - He is a mercenary for hire at the local inn (Can Marry).

Markarth:
Tandir Roseky - He is a guard for the city of Markarth.

Morthal:
Gealhil Forestpool - She is a mercenary for hire at the local inn (Can Marry).

Riften:
Deotwenyl Shadylock - She is a member of the Thieves Guild found in the Ragged Flagon (Can Marry).

Engoagon Barkbranch - He is a member of the Thieves Guild found in the Ragged Flagon (Can Marry).

Metereth Seeddale - She is an instrumental bard at the local inn.

Solitude:
Cingus Softvale - He is a member of the Bards College (can marry)

Dennhiron Dornlock - She is a member of the Bards College (can marry)

Faelwedh Oakenmire - She is a guard for the city of Solitude.

Fimndir Fernlock - He is an adventurer at the local inn (can Marry).

Whiterun:
Allbedir Balfshade - She is a member of the companions and can be found in Jorrvaskr (Can Marry).

Britralorn Lichenstone - He is a member of the companions and can be found in Jorrvaskr (Can Marry).

Winterhold:
Gorcdinor Applescrub - He is a necromancer turned bard at the local inn.

Naeedir Barkwind - She is a mage at the College (Can Marry).

Ungolin Ivywing - He is a mage at the College (Can Marry).

Wilderness:
Areaniir Timbermire - She is a hunter found randomly inbetween cities, occasionally staying in Whiterun.

Bereimir Greenhollow - He is a blind hunter found randomly inbetween cities, occasionally staying in Dawnstar.

Celor Applewind - He is a hunter found randomly inbetween cities, occasionally staying in Windhelm.

Estiragil Duskthorn - She is a mage found randomly inbetween cities (Can Marry).

Thiival Pinedale - She is a hunter found randomly inbetween cities, occasionally staying in Riverwood.

All the content is accesible in default Skyrim, no additional expansions or mods required.

What is added:
-20 wood elves, majority of them marriage candidates.

Changelog:
v1.4:
-Added 2 NPCs to the Bards College
v1.3:
-Changed voice type for the bards (fixed them).
v1.2:
-Fixed minor script efficiency bug on the Thieves Guild and Dark Brotherhood guild members.
-Changed the Thieves Guild members' armor from Leather to Thieves Guild Armor.
-Changed voice type for the guards.
-Added marriage option for the bards.
v1.1:
-Added missing factions to the Hunters
-Added missing Thieves Guild member assault script to the Thieves Guild members.
v1:
-Initial Release

Known Bugs:

None at this time.

Credits:

Bosmer name generator - http://fantasynamegenerators.com/bosmer_names.php


Follow me on Facebook for updates: [url=https://www.facebook.com/ArronDominionProductions/]Arron Dominion Productions[/url]
